[Black "Chapter 7 Kan Formation"]

{Instead of committing the knight to c6, Black opts for an early queenside expansion with ...a6, b5 and Bb7. In the main line, White strikes with 9. Ng5, immediately targeting the weakened e6-square.}

1. e4 c5 2. d4 cxd4 3. c3 dxc3 4. Nxc3 a6 5. Nf3 e6 6. Bc4 b5 {[%entry]} 7. Bb3 Bb7 (7... Nc6 8. O-O Na5 9. Re1 Nxb3 (9... Bb7 10. Bd5) 10. Qxb3) 8. O-O d6 (8... b4 9. Nd5 exd5 10. exd5 Bd6 (10... d6 11. Re1+ Be7 12. Bf4 Kf8 13. Nd4) 11. Re1+ Kf8 12. Bg5 Nf6 13. Qe2) (8... Nc6 9. a4 b4 10. Nd5) 9. Ng5 Nc6 (9... h6 10. Qh5 g6 11. Qh3) 10. f4 (10. Bxe6 fxe6 11. Nxe6 Qd7 12. Nd5 Rc8) 10... Be7 11. f5 Bxg5 12. fxe6 fxe6 13. Qh5+ *
